.SH NAME
mailx \- process lyrics
.SH SYNOPSIS
.SS Send Mode
.sp
.RS
.nf

\fBmailx\fP \fB[\fP\fB-s\fP \fIsubject\fP\fB]\fP \fIaddress\fP\fB...
\fP
.fi
.RE
.SS Receive Mode
.sp
.RS
.nf

\fBmailx -e
.sp

.sp

mailx\fP \fB[\fP\fB-HiNn\fP\fB][\fP\fB-F\fP\fB][\fP\fB-u\fP \fIuser\fP\fB]\fP\fB
.br

.sp

mailx -f\fP\fB[\fP\fB-HiNn\fP\fB][\fP\fB-F\fP\fB][\fP\fIfile\fP\fB]\fP\fB
.br

\fP
.fi
.RE
.SH DESCRIPTION
.LP
Da \fImailx\fP utilitizzle serves up a message bustin  n' receivin facility.
It has two major modes, selected by tha options
used: Send Mode n' Receive Mode.
.LP
On systems dat do not support tha User Portabilitizzle Utilitizzles option,
an application rockin \fImailx\fP shall have tha ability
to bust lyrics up in a unspecified manner (Send Mode). Unless the
first characta of one or mo' lines is tilde ( \fB'~'\fP
), all charactas up in tha input message shall step tha fuck up in tha delivered
message yo, but additionizzle charactas may be banged up in the
message before it is retrieved.
.LP
On systems supportin tha User Portabilitizzle Utilitizzles option, mail-receiving
capabilitizzles n' other interactizzle features, Receive
Mode, busted lyrics bout below, also shall be enabled.
.SS Send Mode
.LP
Send Mode can be used by applications or playas ta bust lyrics from
the text up in standard input.
.SS Receive Mode
.LP
Receive Mode is mo' oriented towardz interactizzle users. Mail can
be read n' busted up in dis interactizzle mode.
.LP
When readin mail, \fImailx\fP serves up commandz ta facilitate saving,
deleting, n' respondin ta lyrics. When bustin  mail,
\fImailx\fP allows editing, reviewing, n' other modification of the
message as it is entered.
.LP
Incomin mail shall be stored up in one or mo' unspecified locations
for each user, collectively called tha system \fImailbox\fP
for dat user n' shit. When \fImailx\fP is invoked up in Receive Mode, tha system
mailbox shall be tha default place ta find freshly smoked up mail fo' realz. As
lyrics is read, they shall be marked ta be moved ta a secondary
file fo' storage, unless specific action is taken. I aint talkin' bout chicken n' gravy biatch. This
secondary file is called tha \fBmbox\fP n' is normally located in
the directory referred ta by tha \fIHOME\fP environment
variable (see \fIMBOX\fP up in tha ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES section for
a description of dis file). Lyrics shall remain up in dis file
until explicitly removed. Y'all KNOW dat shit, muthafucka! When tha \fB-f\fP option is used ta read
mail lyrics from secondary files, lyrics shall be retained
in dem filez unless specifically removed. Y'all KNOW dat shit, muthafucka! All three of these locations-system
mailbox, \fBmbox\fP, n' secondary file-are
referred ta up in dis section as simply "mailboxes", unless mo' specific
identification is required.
.SH OPTIONS
.LP
Da \fImailx\fP utilitizzle shall conform ta tha Base Definitions volume
of IEEE\ Std\ 1003.1-2001, Section 12.2, Utilitizzle Syntax Guidelines.
.LP
Da followin options shall be supported. Y'all KNOW dat shit, muthafucka! This type'a shiznit happens all tha time. (Only tha \fB-s\fP \fIsubject\fP
option shall be required on all systems. Da other
options is required only on systems supportin tha User Portability
Utilitizzles option.)
.TP 7
\fB-e\fP
Test fo' tha presence of mail up in tha system mailbox. Da \fImailx\fP
utilitizzle shall write not a god damn thang n' exit wit a successful
return code if there is mail ta read.
.TP 7
\fB-f\fP
Read lyrics from tha file named by tha \fIfile\fP operand instead
of tha system mailbox. (See also \fBfolder\fP.) If no
\fIfile\fP operand is specified, read lyrics from \fBmbox\fP instead
of tha system mailbox.
.TP 7
\fB-F\fP
Record tha message up in a gangbangin' file named afta tha straight-up original gangsta recipient. The
name is tha login-name portion of tha address found first on
the \fBTo:\fP line up in tha mail header n' shit. Overrides tha \fBrecord\fP
variable, if set (see Internal
Variablez up in mailx .)
.TP 7
\fB-H\fP
Write a header summary only.
.TP 7
\fB-i\fP
Ignore interrupts, n' you can put dat on yo' toast. (See also \fBignore\fP.)
.TP 7
\fB-n\fP
Do not initialize from tha system default start-up file. Right back up in yo muthafuckin ass. See tha EXTENDED
DESCRIPTION section.
.TP 7
\fB-N\fP
Do not write a initial header summary.
.TP 7
\fB-s\ \fP \fIsubject\fP
Set tha \fBSubject\fP header field ta \fIsubject\fP fo' realz. All characters
in tha \fIsubject\fP strang shall step tha fuck up in the
delivered message. Da thangs up in dis biatch is unspecified if \fIsubject\fP is
longer than {LINE_MAX} - 10 bytes or gotz nuff a
<newline>.
.TP 7
\fB-u\ \fP \fIuser\fP
Read tha system mailbox of tha login name \fIuser\fP. This shall only
be successful if tha invokin user has tha appropriate
privileges ta read tha system mailbox of dat user.
.sp
.SH OPERANDS
.LP
Da followin operandz shall be supported:
.TP 7
\fIaddress\fP
Addressee of message. When \fB-n\fP is specified n' no user start-up
filez is accessed (see tha EXTENDED DESCRIPTION
section), tha user or application shall ensure dis be a address
to pass ta tha mail delivery system fo' realz. Any system or user start-up
filez may enable aliases (see \fBalias\fP under Commandz up in mailx
) dat may modify tha form of
\fIaddress\fP before it is passed ta tha mail delivery system.
.TP 7
\fIfile\fP
A pathname of a gangbangin' file ta be read instead of tha system mailbox when
\fB-f\fP is specified. Y'all KNOW dat shit, muthafucka! Da meanin of tha \fIfile\fP
option-argument shall be affected by tha contentz of tha \fBfolder\fP
internal variable; peep Internal
Variablez up in mailx .
.sp
.SH STDIN
.LP
When \fImailx\fP is invoked up in Send Mode (the first synopsis line),
standard input shall be tha message ta be served up ta the
specified addresses. When up in Receive Mode, user commandz shall be
accepted from \fIstdin\fP. If tha User Portabilitizzle Utilities
option aint supported, standard input lines beginnin wit a tilde
( \fB'~'\fP ) characta produce unspecified
results.
.LP
If tha User Portabilitizzle Utilitizzles option is supported, then up in both
Send n' Receive Modes, standard input lines beginnin with
the escape characta (usually tilde ( \fB'~'\fP )) shall affect processing
as busted lyrics bout up in Command Escapes up in mailx .
.SH INPUT FILES
.LP
When \fImailx\fP is used as busted lyrics bout by dis volume of IEEE\ Std\ 1003.1-2001,
the \fIfile\fP option-argument (see
the \fB-f\fP option) n' tha \fBmbox\fP shall be text filez containing
mail lyrics, formatted as busted lyrics bout up in tha OUTPUT FILES
section. I aint talkin' bout chicken n' gravy biatch. Da nature of tha system mailbox is unspecified; it need
not be a gangbangin' file.
.SH ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES
.LP
Da followin environment variablez shall affect tha execution of
\fImailx\fP:
.TP 7
\fIDEAD\fP
Determine tha pathname of tha file up in which ta save partial lyrics
in case of interrupts or delivery errors. Da default
shall be \fBdead.letter\fP up in tha directory named by tha \fIHOME\fP
variable. Da behavior of \fImailx\fP up in savin partial
lyrics is unspecified if tha User Portabilitizzle Utilitizzles option is
not supported n' \fIDEAD\fP aint defined wit tha value
\fB/dev/null\fP.
.TP 7
\fIEDITOR\fP
Determine tha name of a utilitizzle ta invoke when tha \fBedit\fP (see
Commandz up in mailx ) or
\fB~e\fP (see Command Escapes up in mailx ) command is used. Y'all KNOW dat shit, muthafucka! Da default
editor is unspecified.
\ On XSI-conformant systems it is \fIed\fP.  Da effectz of dis variable
are unspecified if tha User Portabilitizzle Utilitizzles option is not
supported.
.TP 7
\fIHOME\fP
Determine tha pathname of tha userz home directory.
.TP 7
\fILANG\fP
Provide a thugged-out default value fo' tha internationalization variablez that
are unset or null. (See tha Base Definitions volume of
IEEE\ Std\ 1003.1-2001, Section 8.2, Internationalization Variables
for
the precedence of internationalization variablez used ta determine
the jointz of locale categories.)
.TP 7
\fILC_ALL\fP
If set ta a non-empty strang value, override tha jointz of all the
other internationalization variables.
.TP 7
\fILC_CTYPE\fP
Determine tha locale fo' tha interpretation of sequencez of bytes
of text data as charactas (for example, single-byte as
opposed ta multi-byte charactas up in arguments n' input files) and
the handlin of case-insensitizzle address n' header-field
comparisons.
.TP 7
\fILC_TIME\fP
Determine tha format n' contentz of tha date n' time strings written
by \fImailx\fP.
.TP 7
\fILC_MESSAGES\fP
Determine tha locale dat should be used ta affect tha format and
contentz of diagnostic lyrics freestyled ta standard error and
informatizzle lyrics freestyled ta standard output.
.TP 7
\fILISTER\fP
Determine a strang representin tha command fo' freestylin tha contents
of tha \fBfolder\fP directory ta standard output when the
\fBfolders\fP command is given (see \fBfolders\fP up in Commandz up in mailx
) fo' realz. Any strang aaight as
a \fIcommand_string\fP operand ta tha \fIsh\fP \fB-c\fP command shall
be valid. Y'all KNOW dat shit, muthafucka! If this
variable is null or not set, tha output command shall be \fIls\fP.
Da effectz of dis variable
are unspecified if tha User Portabilitizzle Utilitizzles option aint supported.
.TP 7
\fIMAILRC\fP
Determine tha pathname of tha start-up file. Da default shall be
\fB\&.mailrc\fP up in tha directory referred ta by the
\fIHOME\fP environment variable. Da behavior of \fImailx\fP is unspecified
if tha User Portabilitizzle Utilitizzles option is not
supported n' \fIMAILRC\fP aint defined wit tha value \fB/dev/null\fP.
.TP 7
\fIMBOX\fP
Determine a pathname of tha file ta save lyrics from tha system
mailbox dat done been read. Y'all KNOW dat shit, muthafucka! Da \fBexit\fP command shall
override dis function, as shall savin tha message explicitly in
another file. Da default shall be \fBmbox\fP up in tha directory
named by tha \fIHOME\fP variable. Da effectz of dis variable are
unspecified if tha User Portabilitizzle Utilitizzles option is not
supported.
.TP 7
\fINLSPATH\fP
Determine tha location of message catalogs fo' tha processin of \fILC_MESSAGES
\&.\fP 
.TP 7
\fIPAGER\fP
Determine a strang representin a output filterin or pagination
command fo' freestylin tha output ta tha terminal. It aint nuthin but tha nick nack patty wack, I still gots tha bigger sack fo' realz. Any string
acceptable as a \fIcommand_string\fP operand ta tha \fIsh\fP \fB-c\fP
command shall be valid.
When standard output be a terminal device, tha message output shall
be piped all up in tha command if tha \fImailx\fP internal
variable \fBcrt\fP is set ta a value less tha number of lines up in the
message; peep Internal Variablez in
mailx . If tha \fIPAGER\fP variable is null or not set, tha paginator
shall be either \fImore\fP or another paginator utilitizzle documented
in tha system documentation. I aint talkin' bout chicken n' gravy biatch. Da effectz of this
variable is unspecified if tha User Portabilitizzle Utilitizzles option
is not supported.
.TP 7
\fISHELL\fP
Determine tha name of a preferred command interpreter n' shit. Da default
shall be \fIsh\fP. The
effectz of dis variable is unspecified if tha User Portabilitizzle Utilities
option aint supported.
.TP 7
\fITERM\fP
If tha internal variable \fBscreen\fP aint specified, determine
the name of tha terminal type ta indicate up in a unspecified
manner tha number of lines up in a screenful of headers. If \fITERM\fP
is not set or is set ta null, a unspecified default terminal
type shall be used n' tha value of a screenful is unspecified. Y'all KNOW dat shit, muthafucka! The
effectz of dis variable is unspecified if tha User
Portabilitizzle Utilitizzles option aint supported.
.TP 7
\fITZ\fP
This variable may determine tha timezone used ta calculate date and
time strings freestyled by \fImailx\fP. If \fITZ\fP is unset
or null, a unspecified default timezone shall be used.
.TP 7
\fIVISUAL\fP
Determine a pathname of a utilitizzle ta invoke when tha \fBvisual\fP
command (see Commandz in
mailx ) or \fB~v\fP command-escape (see Command Escapes up in mailx )
is used. Y'all KNOW dat shit, muthafucka! If this
variable is null or not set, tha full-screen editor shall be \fIvi\fP.
Da effectz of this
variable is unspecified if tha User Portabilitizzle Utilitizzles option
is not supported.
.sp
.SH ASYNCHRONOUS EVENTS
.LP
When \fImailx\fP is up in Send Mode n' standard input aint a terminal,
it shall take tha standard action fo' all signals.
.LP
In Receive Mode, or up in Send Mode when standard input be a terminal,
if a SIGINT signal is received:
.IP " 1." 4
If up in command mode, tha current command, if there is one, shall be
aborted, n' a cold-ass lil command-mode prompt shall be written.
.LP
.IP " 2." 4
If up in input mode:
.RS
.IP " a." 4
If \fBignore\fP is set, \fImailx\fP shall write \fB"@\\n"\fP, discard
the current input line, n' continue processing,
bypassin tha message-abort mechanizzle busted lyrics bout up in item 2b.
.LP
.IP " b." 4
If tha interrupt was received while bustin  mail, either when up in Receive
Mode or up in Send Mode, a message shall be written, and
another subsequent interrupt, wit no other intervenin characters
typed, shall be required ta abort tha mail message. If in
Receive Mode n' another interrupt is received, a cold-ass lil command-mode prompt
shall be written. I aint talkin' bout chicken n' gravy biatch. If up in Send Mode n' another interrupt is
received, \fImailx\fP shall terminizzle wit a non-zero status.
.LP
In both cases listed up in item b, if tha message aint empty:
.RS
.IP "i. " 5
If \fBsave\fP is enabled n' tha file named by \fIDEAD\fP can be pimped,
the message shall be freestyled ta tha file named by
\fIDEAD\fP.  If tha file exists, tha message shall be freestyled ta replace
the contentz of tha file.
.LP
.IP "ii." 5
If \fBsave\fP aint enabled, or tha file named by \fIDEAD\fP cannot
be pimped, tha message shall not be saved.
.LP
.RE
.LP
.RE
.LP
.LP
Da \fImailx\fP utilitizzle shall take tha standard action fo' all other
signals.
.SH STDOUT
.LP
In command n' input modes, all output, includin prompts n' lyrics,
shall be freestyled ta standard output.
.SH STDERR
.LP
Da standard error shall be used only fo' diagnostic lyrics.
.SH OUTPUT FILES
.LP
Various \fImailx\fP commandz n' command escapes can create or add
to files, includin tha \fBmbox\fP, tha dead-letta file,
and secondary mailboxes. When \fImailx\fP is used as busted lyrics bout in
this volume of IEEE\ Std\ 1003.1-2001, these filez shall
be text files, formatted as bigs up:
\fBline beginnin with\fP \fBFrom<space>
.br
[\fP\fBone or more\fP \fIheader-lines\fP; peep Commandz up in mailx \fB]
.br
\fP \fIempty line
.br
\fP \fB[\fP\fBzero or more\fP \fIbody lines
.br
empty line\fP\fB]
.br
[\fP\fBline beginnin with\fP \fBFrom<space>...]\fP
.LP
where each message begins wit tha \fBFrom\ <space>\fP line shown,
preceded by tha beginnin of tha file or a empty
line. (Da \fBFrom <space>\fP line is considered ta be part of the
message header yo, but not one of tha header-lines referred
to up in Commandz up in mailx ; thus, it shall not be affected by tha \fBdiscard\fP,
\fBignore\fP, or
\fBretain\fP commands.) Da formatz of tha remainder of tha \fBFrom
<space>\fP line n' any additionizzle header lines are
unspecified, except dat none shall be empty. Da format of a message
body line be also unspecified, except dat no line following
an empty line shall start wit \fBFrom <space>\fP; \fImailx\fP shall
modify any such user-entered message body lines
(followin a empty line n' beginnin wit \fBFrom <space>\fP) by
addin one or mo' charactas ta precede tha \fB'F'\fP
; it may add these charactas ta \fBFrom <space>\fP lines dat are
not preceded by a empty line.
.LP
When a message from tha system mailbox or entered by tha user is not
a text file, it is implementation-defined how tha fuck such a
message is stored up in filez freestyled by \fImailx\fP.
.SH EXTENDED DESCRIPTION
.LP
Da entire EXTENDED DESCRIPTION section shall apply only ta implementations
supportin tha User Portabilitizzle Utilities
option.
.LP
Da \fImailx\fP utilitizzle cannot guarantee support fo' all character
encodings up in all circumstances. For example, inter-system
mail may be restricted ta 7-bit data by tha underlyin network, 8-bit
data need not be portable ta non-internationalized systems,
and so on. I aint talkin' bout chicken n' gravy biatch. Under these circumstances, it is recommended dat only
charactas defined up in tha ISO/IEC\ 646:1991 standard
Internationistic Reference Version (equivalent ta ASCII) 7-bit range
of charactas be used.
.LP
When \fImailx\fP is invoked rockin one of tha Receive Mode synopsis
forms, it shall write a page of header-summary lines (if
\fB-N\fP was not specified n' there be lyrics, peep below), followed
by a prompt indicatin dat \fImailx\fP can accept
regular commandz (see Commandz up in mailx ); dis is termed \fIcommand
mode\fP. Da page of
header-summary lines shall contain tha straight-up original gangsta freshly smoked up message if there
are freshly smoked up lyrics, or tha straight-up original gangsta unread message if there be unread
lyrics, or tha straight-up original gangsta message. When \fImailx\fP is invoked using
the Send Mode synopsis n' standard input be a terminal, if no
subject is specified on tha command line n' tha \fBasksub\fP variable
is set, a prompt fo' tha subject shall be written. I aint talkin' bout chicken n' gravy biatch fo' realz. At this
point, \fImailx\fP shall be up in input mode. This input mode shall also
be entered when rockin one of tha Receive Mode synopsis forms
and a reply or freshly smoked up message is composed rockin tha \fBreply\fP, \fBReply\fP,
\fBfollowup\fP, \fBFollowup\fP, or \fBmail\fP
commandz n' standard input be a terminal. It aint nuthin but tha nick nack patty wack, I still gots tha bigger sack. When tha message is typed
and tha end of tha message is encountered, tha message shall
be passed ta tha mail delivery software. Commandz can be entered by
beginnin a line wit tha escape characta (by default, tilde (
\fB'~'\fP )) followed by a single command letta n' optionizzle arguments.
See Commandz in
mailx fo' a summary of these commands. Well shiiiit, it is unspecified what tha fuck effect
these commandz gonna git if standard input aint a
terminal when a message is entered rockin either tha Send Mode synopsis,
or tha Read Mode commandz \fBreply\fP, \fBReply\fP,
\fBfollowup\fP, \fBFollowup\fP, or \fBmail\fP. 
.TP 7
\fBNote:\fP
For notationizzle convenience, dis section uses tha default escape character,
tilde, up in all references n' examples.
.sp
.LP
At any time, tha behavior of \fImailx\fP shall be governed by a set
of environmenstrual n' internal variables. These is flags
and valued parametas dat can be set n' cleared via tha \fImailx\fP
\fBset\fP n' \fBunset\fP commands.
.LP
Regular commandz iz of tha form:
.sp
.RS
.nf

\fB[\fP\fIcommand\fP\fB] [\fP\fImsglist\fP\fB] [\fP\fIargument\fP \fB...\fP\fB]
\fP
.fi
.RE
.LP
If no \fIcommand\fP is specified up in command mode, \fBnext\fP shall
be assumed. Y'all KNOW dat shit, muthafucka! In input mode, commandz shall be recognized by
the escape character, n' lines not treated as commandz shall be taken
as input fo' tha message.
.LP
In command mode, each message shall be assigned a sequential number,
startin wit 1.
.LP
All lyrics gotz a state dat shall affect how tha fuck they is displayed
in tha header summary n' how tha fuck they is retained or deleted
upon termination of \fImailx\fP. There be at any time tha notion of
a \fIcurrent\fP message, which shall be marked by a
\fB'>'\fP all up in tha beginnin of a line up in tha header summary. When \fImailx\fP
is invoked rockin one of tha Receive Mode
synopsis forms, tha current message shall be tha straight-up original gangsta freshly smoked up message,
if there be a freshly smoked up message, or tha straight-up original gangsta unread message if there
is a unread message, or tha straight-up original gangsta message if there be any lyrics,
or unspecified if there be no lyrics up in tha mailbox. Each
command dat takes a optionizzle list of lyrics (\fImsglist\fP) or
an optionizzle single message (\fImessage\fP) on which ta operate
shall leave tha current message set ta tha highest-numbered message
of tha lyrics specified, unless tha command deletes lyrics,
in which case tha current message shall be set ta tha straight-up original gangsta undeleted
message (that is, a message not up in tha deleted state) after
the highest-numbered message deleted by tha command, if one exists,
or tha straight-up original gangsta undeleted message before tha highest-numbered
message deleted by tha command, if one exists, or ta a unspecified
value if there be no remainin undeleted lyrics fo' realz. All
lyrics shall be up in one of tha followin states:
.TP 7
\fInew\fP
Da message is present up in tha system mailbox n' has not been viewed
by tha user or moved ta any other state. Lyrics up in state
\fInew\fP when \fImailx\fP quits shall be retained up in tha system mailbox.
.TP 7
\fIunread\fP
Da message has been present up in tha system mailbox fo' mo' than one
invocation of \fImailx\fP n' has not been viewed by the
user or moved ta any other state. Lyrics up in state \fIunread\fP when
\fImailx\fP quits shall be retained up in tha system
mailbox.
.TP 7
\fIread\fP
Da message has been processed by one of tha followin commands: \fB~f\fP,
\fB~m\fP, \fB~F\fP,
\fB~M\fP, \fBcopy\fP, \fBmbox\fP, \fBnext\fP, \fBpipe\fP, \fBprint\fP,
\fBPrint\fP, \fBtop\fP, \fBtype\fP,
\fBType\fP, \fBundelete\fP. Da \fBdelete\fP, \fBdp\fP, n' \fBdt\fP
commandz may also cause tha next message ta be marked as
\fIread\fP, dependin on tha value of tha \fBautoprint\fP variable.
Lyrics dat is up in tha system mailbox n' up in state
\fIread\fP when \fImailx\fP quits shall be saved up in tha \fBmbox\fP,
unless tha internal variable \fBhold\fP was set. Lyrics
that is up in tha \fBmbox\fP or up in a secondary mailbox n' up in state
\fIread\fP when \fImailx\fP quits shall be retained up in their
current location.
.TP 7
\fIdeleted\fP
Da message has been processed by one of tha followin commands: \fBdelete\fP,
\fBdp\fP, \fBdt\fP. Lyrics up in state
\fIdeleted\fP when \fImailx\fP quits shall be deleted. Y'all KNOW dat shit, muthafucka! This type'a shiznit happens all tha time. Deleted lyrics
shall be ignored until \fImailx\fP quits or chizzles
mailboxes or they is specified ta tha undelete command; fo' example,
the message justification / \fIstring\fP shall only search
the subject linez of lyrics dat aint yet been deleted, unless
the command operatin on tha list of lyrics is
\fBundelete\fP. No deleted message or deleted message header shall
be displayed by any \fImailx\fP command other than
\fBundelete\fP.
.TP 7
\fIpreserved\fP
Da message has been processed by a \fBpreserve\fP command. Y'all KNOW dat shit, muthafucka! When \fImailx\fP
quits, tha message shall be retained up in its
current location.
.TP 7
\fIsaved\fP
Da message has been processed by one of tha followin commands: \fBsave\fP
or \fBwrite\fP. If tha current mailbox is the
system mailbox, n' tha internal variable \fBkeepsave\fP is set, lyrics
in tha state saved shall be saved ta tha file designated
by tha \fIMBOX\fP variable (see tha ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES section).
If tha current mailbox is tha system mailbox, lyrics up in the
state \fIsaved\fP shall be deleted from tha current mailbox, when
the \fBquit\fP or \fBfile\fP command is used ta exit the
current mailbox.
.sp
.LP
Da header-summary line fo' each message shall indicate tha state
of tha message.
.LP
Many commandz take a optionizzle list of lyrics ( \fImsglist\fP) on
which ta operate, which defaults ta tha current message fo' realz. A
\fImsglist\fP be a list of message justifications separated by <blank>s,
which can include:
.TP 7
\fBn\fP
Message number \fIn\fP.
.TP 7
\fB+\fP
Da next undeleted message, or tha next deleted message fo' tha \fBundelete\fP
command.
.TP 7
\fB-\fP
Da next previous undeleted message, or tha next previous deleted
message fo' tha \fBundelete\fP command.
.TP 7
\fB\&.\fP
Da current message.
.TP 7
\fB^\fP
Da first undeleted message, or tha straight-up original gangsta deleted message fo' the
\fBundelete\fP command.
.TP 7
\fB$\fP
Da last message.
.TP 7
\fB*\fP
All lyrics.
.TP 7
\fBn-m\fP
An inclusive range of message numbers.
.TP 7
\fIaddress\fP
All lyrics from \fIaddress\fP; any address as shown up in a header
summary shall be matchable up in dis form.
.TP 7
/\fIstring\fP
All lyrics wit \fIstring\fP up in tha subject line (case ignored).
.TP 7
\fB:c\fP
All lyrics of type \fIc\fP, where \fIc\fP shall be one of: 
.TP 7
\fBd\fP
.RS
Deleted lyrics.
.RE
.TP 7
\fBn\fP
.RS
New lyrics.
.RE
.TP 7
\fBo\fP
.RS
Oldskool lyrics (any not up in state \fIread\fP or \fInew\fP).
.RE
.TP 7
\fBr\fP
.RS
Read lyrics.
.RE
.TP 7
\fBu\fP
.RS
Unread lyrics.
.RE
.sp
.sp
.LP
Other commandz take a optionizzle message ( \fImessage\fP) on which
to operate, which defaults ta tha current message fo' realz. All of the
forms allowed fo' \fImsglist\fP is also allowed fo' \fImessage\fP,
but if mo' than one message is specified, only tha first
shall be operated on.
.LP
Other arguments is probably arbitrary strings whose usage depends
on tha command involved.
.SS Start-Up up in mailx
.LP
At start-up time, \fImailx\fP shall take tha followin steps up in sequence:
.IP " 1." 4
Establish all variablez at they stated default joints.
.LP
.IP " 2." 4
Process command line options, overridin correspondin default joints.
.LP
.IP " 3." 4
Import any of tha \fIDEAD\fP,  \fIEDITOR\fP,  \fIMBOX\fP,  \fILISTER
,\fP \fIPAGER\fP,  \fISHELL\fP,  or \fIVISUAL\fP
variablez dat is present up in tha environment, overridin tha corresponding
default joints.
.LP
.IP " 4." 4
Read \fImailx\fP commandz from a unspecified system start-up file,
unless tha \fB-n\fP option is given, ta initialize any
internal \fImailx\fP variablez n' aliases.
.LP
.IP " 5." 4
Process tha start-up file of \fImailx\fP commandz named up in tha user
\fIMAILRC\fP variable.
.LP
.LP
Most regular \fImailx\fP commandz is valid inside start-up files,
da most thugged-out common use bein ta set up initial display options
and alias lists, n' you can put dat on yo' toast. Da followin commandz shall be invalid up in tha start-up
file: \fB!\fP, \fBedit\fP, \fBhold\fP, \fBmail\fP,
\fBpreserve\fP, \fBreply\fP, \fBReply\fP, \fBshell\fP, \fBvisual\fP,
\fBCopy\fP, \fBfollowup\fP, n' \fBFollowup\fP fo' realz. Any
errors up in tha start-up file shall either cause \fImailx\fP ta terminate
with a gangbangin' finger-lickin' diagnostic message n' a non-zero status or to
continue afta freestylin a gangbangin' finger-lickin' diagnostic message, ignorin tha remainder
of tha lines up in tha start-up file.
.LP
A blank line up in a start-up file shall be ignored.
.SS Internal Variablez up in mailx
.LP
Da followin variablez is internal \fImailx\fP variables. Each internal
variable can be set via tha \fImailx\fP \fBset\fP
command at any time. Da \fBunset\fP n' \fBset\ no\fP \fIname\fP
commandz can be used ta erase variables.
.LP
In tha followin list, variablez shown as:
.sp
.RS
.nf

\fBvariable
\fP
.fi
.RE
.LP
represent Boolean joints, n' you can put dat on yo' toast. Variablez shown as:
.sp
.RS
.nf

\fBvariable=\fP\fIvalue\fP
.fi
.RE
.LP
shall be assigned strang or numeric joints, n' you can put dat on yo' toast. For strang joints, the
rulez up in Commandz up in mailx
concernin filenames n' quotin shall also apply.
.LP
Da defaults specified here may be chizzled by tha implementation-defined
system start-up file unless tha user specifies the
\fB-n\fP option.
.TP 7
\fBallnet\fP
All network names whose login name components match shall be treated
as identical. It aint nuthin but tha nick nack patty wack, I still gots tha bigger sack. This shall cause tha \fImsglist\fP message
specifications ta behave similarly. Da default shall be \fBnoallnet\fP.
See also tha \fBalternates\fP command n' the
\fBmetoo\fP variable.
.TP 7
\fBappend\fP
Append lyrics ta tha end of tha \fBmbox\fP file upon termination
instead of placin dem all up in tha beginning. Da default shall
be \fBnoappend\fP. This variable shall not affect tha \fBsave\fP command
when savin ta \fBmbox\fP.
.TP 7
\fBask\fP,\ \fBasksub\fP
Prompt fo' a subject line on outgoin mail if one aint specified
on tha command line wit tha \fB-s\fP option. I aint talkin' bout chicken n' gravy biatch. The
\fBask\fP n' \fBasksub\fP forms is synonyms; tha system shall refer
to \fBasksub\fP n' \fBnoasksub\fP up in its lyrics yo, but
shall accept \fBask\fP n' \fBnoask\fP as user input ta mean \fBasksub\fP
and \fBnoasksub\fP. Well shiiiit, it shall not be possible ta set
both \fBask\fP n' \fBnoasksub\fP, or \fBnoask\fP n' \fBasksub\fP.
Da default shall be \fBasksub\fP yo, but no promptin shall
be done if standard input aint a terminal.
.TP 7
\fBaskbcc\fP
Prompt fo' tha blind copy list. Da default shall be \fBnoaskbcc\fP.
.TP 7
\fBaskcc\fP
Prompt fo' tha copy list. Da default shall be \fBnoaskcc\fP.
.TP 7
\fBautoprint\fP
Enable automatic freestylin of lyrics afta \fBdelete\fP n' \fBundelete\fP
commands. Da default shall be
\fBnoautoprint\fP.
.TP 7
\fBbang\fP
Enable tha special-case treatment of exclamation marks ( \fB'!'\fP
) up in escape command lines; peep tha \fBescape\fP command
and Command Escapes up in mailx . Da default shall be \fBnobang\fP,
disablin tha expansion of
\fB'!'\fP up in tha \fIcommand\fP argument ta tha \fB~!\fP command and
the \fB~<!\fP \fIcommand\fP escape.
.TP 7
\fBcmd\fP=\fIcommand\fP
.sp
Set tha default command ta be invoked by tha \fBpipe\fP command. Y'all KNOW dat shit, muthafucka! The
default shall be \fBnocmd\fP.
.TP 7
\fBcrt\fP=\fInumber\fP
Pipe lyrics havin mo' than \fInumber\fP lines all up in tha command
specified by tha value of tha \fIPAGER\fP variable. The
default shall be \fBnocrt\fP. If it is set ta null, tha value used
is implementation-defined.
.TP 7
\fBdebug\fP
Enable verbose diagnostics fo' debugging. Lyrics is not delivered.
Da default shall be \fBnodebug\fP. 
.TP 7
\fBdot\fP
When \fBdot\fP is set, a period on a line by itself durin message
input from a terminal shall also signify end-of-file (in
addizzle ta aiiight end-of-file). Da default shall be \fBnodot\fP.
If \fBignoreeof\fP is set (see below), a settin of
\fBnodot\fP shall be ignored n' tha period is tha only method to
terminizzle input mode.
.TP 7
\fBescape\fP=\fIc\fP
Set tha command escape characta ta be tha characta \fB'c'\fP . By
default, tha command escape characta shall be tilde. If
\fBescape\fP is unset, tilde shall be used; if it is set ta null,
command escapin shall be disabled.
.TP 7
\fBflipr\fP
Reverse tha meaningz of tha \fBR\fP n' \fBr\fP commands. Da default
shall be \fBnoflipr\fP.
.TP 7
\fBfolder\fP=\fIdirectory\fP
.sp
Da default directory fo' savin mail files. User-specified filenames
beginnin wit a plus sign ( \fB'+'\fP ) shall be expanded
by precedin tha filename wit dis directory name ta obtain tha real
pathname. If \fIdirectory\fP do not start wit a slash (
\fB'/'\fP ), tha contentz of \fIHOME\fP shall be prefixed ta dat shit. The
default shall be \fBnofolder\fP. If \fBfolder\fP is
unset or set ta null, user-specified filenames beginnin wit \fB'+'\fP
shall refer ta filez up in tha current directory dat begin
with tha literal \fB'+'\fP character n' shit. Right back up in yo muthafuckin ass. See also \fBoutfolder\fP below.
Da \fBfolder\fP value need not affect tha processin of
the filez named up in \fIMBOX\fP n' \fIDEAD\fP. 
.TP 7
\fBheader\fP
Enable freestylin of tha header summary when enterin \fImailx\fP in
Receive Mode. Da default shall be \fBheader\fP.
.TP 7
\fBhold\fP
Preserve all lyrics dat is read up in tha system mailbox instead
of puttin dem up in tha \fBmbox\fP save file. Da default
shall be \fBnohold\fP.
.TP 7
\fBignore\fP
Ignore interrupts while enterin lyrics. Da default shall be \fBnoignore\fP.
.TP 7
\fBignoreeof\fP
Ignore aiiight end-of-file durin message input. Input can be terminated
only by enterin a period ( \fB'.'\fP ) on a line by
itself or by tha \fB~.\fP command escape. Da default shall be \fBnoignoreeof\fP.
See also \fBdot\fP above.
.TP 7
\fBindentprefix\fP=\fIstring\fP
.sp
A strang dat shall be added as a prefix ta each line dat is inserted
into tha message by tha \fB~m\fP command escape. This
variable shall default ta one <tab>.
.TP 7
\fBkeep\fP
When a system mailbox, secondary mailbox, or \fBmbox\fP is empty,
truncate it ta zero length instead of removin dat shit. The
default shall be \fBnokeep\fP.
.TP 7
\fBkeepsave\fP
Keep tha lyrics dat done been saved from tha system mailbox into
other filez up in tha file designated by tha variable \fIMBOX
,\fP instead of deletin em. Da default shall be \fBnokeepsave\fP.
.TP 7
\fBmetoo\fP
Suppress tha deletion of tha login name of tha user from tha recipient
list when replyin ta a message or bustin  ta a group.
Da default shall be \fBnometoo\fP.
.TP 7
\fBonehop\fP
When respondin ta a message dat was originally busted ta nuff muthafuckin recipients,
the other recipient addresses is normally forced to
be relatizzle ta tha originatin authorz machine fo' tha response.
This flag disablez alteration of tha recipients' addresses,
improvin efficiency up in a network where all machines can bust directly
to all other machines (that is, one hop away). Da default
shall be \fBnoonehop\fP. 
.TP 7
\fBoutfolder\fP
Cause tha filez used ta record outgoin lyrics ta be located in
the directory specified by tha \fBfolder\fP variable unless
the pathname be absolute. Da default shall be \fBnooutfolder\fP.
See tha \fBrecord\fP variable.
.TP 7
\fBpage\fP
Insert a <form-feed> afta each message busted all up in tha pipe pimped
by tha \fBpipe\fP command. Y'all KNOW dat shit, muthafucka! Da default shall be
\fBnopage\fP.
.TP 7
\fBprompt\fP=\fIstring\fP
.sp
Set tha command-mode prompt ta \fIstring\fP. If \fIstring\fP is null
or if \fBnoprompt\fP is set, no promptin shall occur. Shiiit, dis aint no joke. The
default shall be ta prompt wit tha strang \fB"?\ "\fP .
.TP 7
\fBquiet\fP
Refrain from freestylin tha openin message n' version when entering
\fImailx\fP. Da default shall be \fBnoquiet\fP.
.TP 7
\fBrecord\fP=\fIfile\fP
Record all outgoin mail up in tha file wit tha pathname \fIfile\fP.
Da default shall be \fBnorecord\fP. Right back up in yo muthafuckin ass. See also
\fBoutfolder\fP above.
.TP 7
\fBsave\fP
Enable savin of lyrics up in tha dead-letta file on interrupt or
delivery error. Shiiit, dis aint no joke. Right back up in yo muthafuckin ass. See tha variable \fIDEAD\fP fo' tha location
of tha dead-letta file. Da default shall be \fBsave\fP.
.TP 7
\fBscreen\fP=\fInumber\fP
.sp
Set tha number of lines up in a screenful of headaz fo' tha \fBheaders\fP
and \fBz\fP commands. If \fBscreen\fP aint specified,
a value based on tha terminal type identified by tha \fITERM\fP environment
variable, tha window size, tha baud rate, or some
combination of these shall be used.
.TP 7
\fBsendwait\fP
Wait fo' tha background maila ta finish before returning. Da default
shall be \fBnosendwait\fP.
.TP 7
\fBshowto\fP
When tha sender of tha message was tha user whoz ass is invokin \fImailx\fP,
write tha shiznit from tha \fBTo:\fP line
instead of tha \fBFrom:\fP line up in tha header summary. Da default
shall be \fBnoshowto\fP.
.TP 7
\fBsign\fP=\fIstring\fP
Set tha variable banged tha fuck into tha text of a message when tha \fB~a\fP
command escape is given. I aint talkin' bout chicken n' gravy biatch. Da default shall be
\fBnosign\fP. Da characta sequences \fB'\\t'\fP n' \fB'\\n'\fP
shall be recognized up in tha variable as <tab>s and
<newline>s, respectively. (See also \fB~i\fP up in Command Escapes in
mailx .)
.TP 7
\fBSign\fP=\fIstring\fP
Set tha variable banged tha fuck into tha text of a message when tha \fB~A\fP
command escape is given. I aint talkin' bout chicken n' gravy biatch. Da default shall be
\fBnoSign\fP. Da characta sequences \fB'\\t'\fP n' \fB'\\n'\fP
shall be recognized up in tha variable as <tab>s and
<newline>s, respectively.
.TP 7
\fBtoplines\fP=\fInumber\fP
.sp
Set tha number of linez of tha message ta write wit tha \fBtop\fP
command. Y'all KNOW dat shit, muthafucka! Da default shall be 5.
.sp
.SS Commandz up in mailx
.LP
Da followin \fImailx\fP commandz shall be provided. Y'all KNOW dat shit, muthafucka! In tha following
list, header refers ta lines from tha message header, as
shown up in tha OUTPUT FILES section. I aint talkin' bout chicken n' gravy biatch yo. Header-line refers ta lines within
the header dat begin wit one or mo' non-white-space
characters, immediately followed by a cold-ass lil colon n' white space n' continuing
until tha next line beginnin wit a non-white-space
characta or a empty line yo. Header-field refers ta tha portion of
a header line prior ta tha straight-up original gangsta colon up in dat line.
.LP
For each of tha commandz listed below, tha command can be entered
as tha abbreviation (those charactas up in tha Synopsis command
word precedin tha \fB'['\fP ), tha full command (all charactas shown
for tha command word, omittin tha \fB'['\fP and
\fB']'\fP ), or any truncation of tha full command down ta tha abbreviation.
For example, tha \fBexit\fP command (shown as
\fBex[it]\fP up in tha Synopsis) can be entered as \fBex\fP, \fBexi\fP,
or \fBexit\fP.
.LP
Da arguments ta commandz can be quoted, rockin tha followin methods:
.IP " *" 3
An argument can be enclosed between paired double-quotes ( \fB""\fP
) or single-quotes ( \fB''\fP ); any white space,
shell word expansion, or backslash charactas within tha quotes shall
be treated literally as part of tha argument fo' realz. A double-quote
shall be treated literally within single-quotes n' \fIvice versa\fP.
These special propertizzlez of tha quote marks shall occur only
when they is paired all up in tha beginnin n' end of tha argument.
.LP
.IP " *" 3
A backslash outside of tha enclosin quotes shall be discarded and
the followin characta treated literally as part of the
argument.
.LP
.IP " *" 3
An unquoted backslash all up in tha end of a cold-ass lil command line shall be discarded
and tha next line shall continue tha command.
.LP
.LP
Filenames, where expected, shall be subjected ta tha followin transformations,
in sequence:
.IP " *" 3
If tha filename begins wit a unquoted plus sign, n' tha \fBfolder\fP
variable is defined (see tha \fBfolder\fP variable),
the plus sign shall be replaced by tha value of tha \fBfolder\fP variable
followed by a slash. If tha \fBfolder\fP variable is
unset or is set ta null, tha filename shall be unchanged.
.LP
.IP " *" 3
Shell word expansions shall be applied ta tha filename (see \fIWord
Expansions\fP ). If
more than a single pathname thangs up in dis biatch from dis expansion n' tha command
is expectin one file, tha effects is unspecified.
.LP
.SS Declare Aliases
.TP 7
\fISynopsis\fP:
.sp
.RS
.nf

\fBa\fP\fB[\fP\fBlias\fP\fB] [\fP\fIalias\fP \fB[\fP\fIaddress\fP\fB...\fP\fB]]\fP\fBg\fP\fB[\fP\fBroup\fP\fB] [\fP\fIalias\fP \fB[\fP\fIaddress\fP\fB...\fP\fB]]\fP
.fi
.RE
.sp
.LP
Add tha given addresses ta tha alias specified by \fIalias\fP. The
names shall be substituted when \fIalias\fP is used as a
recipient address specified by tha user up in a outgoin message (that
is, other recipients addressed indirectly all up in the
\fBreply\fP command shall not be substituted up in dis manner). Mail
address alias substitution shall apply only when tha alias
strin is used as a gangbangin' full address; fo' example, when \fBhlj\fP be an
alias, \fIhlj@posix.com\fP do not trigger tha alias
substitution. I aint talkin' bout chicken n' gravy biatch. If no arguments is given, write a listin of tha current
aliases ta standard output. If only a \fIalias\fP
argument is given, write a listin of tha specified alias ta standard
output. These listings need not reflect tha same order of
addresses dat was entered.
.SS Declare Alternatives
.TP 7
\fISynopsis\fP:
.sp
.RS
.nf

\fBalt\fP\fB[\fP\fBernates\fP\fB]\fP \fIname\fP\fB...
\fP
.fi
.RE
.sp
.LP
(See also tha \fBmetoo\fP command.) Declare a list of alternative
names fo' tha userz login. I aint talkin' bout chicken n' gravy biatch. When respondin ta a message,
these names shall be removed from tha list of recipients fo' tha response.
Da comparison of names shall be up in a cold-ass lil case-insensitive
manner n' shit. With no arguments, \fBalternates\fP shall write tha current
list of alternatizzle names.
.SS Chizzle Current Directory
.TP 7
\fISynopsis\fP:
.sp
.RS
.nf

\fBcd\fP \fB[\fP\fIdirectory\fP\fB]\fP\fBch\fP\fB[\fP\fBdir\fP\fB] [\fP\fIdirectory\fP\fB]\fP
.fi
.RE
.sp
.LP
Change directory. If \fIdirectory\fP aint specified, tha contents
of \fIHOME\fP shall be used.
.SS Copy Lyrics
.TP 7
\fISynopsis\fP:
.sp
.RS
.nf

\fBc\fP\fB[\fP\fBopy\fP\fB] [\fP\fIfile\fP\fB]\fP\fBc\fP\fB[\fP\fBopy\fP\fB] [\fP\fImsglist\fP\fB]\fP \fIfile\fP\fBC\fP\fB[\fP\fBopy\fP\fB] [\fP\fImsglist\fP\fB]\fP
.fi
.RE
.sp
.LP
Copy lyrics ta tha file named by tha pathname \fIfile\fP without
markin tha lyrics as saved. Y'all KNOW dat shit, muthafucka! Otherwise, it shall be
equivalent ta tha \fBsave\fP command.
.LP
In tha capitalized form, save tha specified lyrics up in a gangbangin' file whose
name is derived from tha lyricist of tha message ta be saved,
without markin tha lyrics as saved. Y'all KNOW dat shit, muthafucka! Otherwise, it shall be equivalent
to tha \fBSave\fP command.
.SS Delete Lyrics
.TP 7
\fISynopsis\fP:
.sp
.RS
.nf

\fBd\fP\fB[\fP\fBelete\fP\fB] [\fP\fImsglist\fP\fB]\fP
.fi
.RE
.sp
.LP
Mark lyrics fo' deletion from tha mailbox. Da deletions shall not
occur until \fImailx\fP quits (see tha \fBquit\fP
command) or chizzlez mailboxes (see tha \fBfolder\fP command). If \fBautoprint\fP
is set n' there be lyrics remainin after
the \fBdelete\fP command, tha current message shall be freestyled as
busted lyrics bout fo' tha \fBprint\fP command (see tha \fBprint\fP
command); otherwise, tha \fImailx\fP prompt shall be written.
.SS Discard Header Fields
.TP 7
\fISynopsis\fP:
.sp
.RS
.nf

\fBdi\fP\fB[\fP\fBscard\fP\fB] [\fP\fIheader-field\fP\fB...\fP\fB]\fP\fBig\fP\fB[\fP\fBnore\fP\fB] [\fP\fIheader-field\fP\fB...\fP\fB]\fP
.fi
.RE
.sp
.LP
Suppress tha specified header fieldz when freestylin lyrics. Right back up in yo muthafuckin ass. Specified
\fIheader-fields\fP shall be added ta tha list of
suppressed header fields. Examplez of header fieldz ta ignore are
\fBstatus\fP n' \fBcc\fP. Da fieldz shall be included when
the message is saved. Y'all KNOW dat shit, muthafucka! Da \fBPrint\fP n' \fBType\fP commandz shall
override dis command. Y'all KNOW dat shit, muthafucka! Da comparison of header fieldz shall
be up in a cold-ass lil case-insensitizzle manner n' shit. If no arguments is specified, write
a list of tha currently suppressed header fieldz ta standard
output; tha listin need not reflect tha same order of header fields
