.SS Command Escapes up in mailx
.LP
Da followin commandz can be entered only from input mode, by beginning
a line wit tha escape characta (by default, tilde (
\fB'~'\fP )). Right back up in yo muthafuckin ass. See tha \fBescape\fP variable description fo' changing
this special character n' shit. Da format fo' tha commands
shall be:
.sp
.RS
.nf

\fB<\fP\fIescape-character\fP\fB><\fP\fIcommand-char\fP\fB><\fP\fIseparator\fP\fB>\fP\fB[\fP\fB<\fP\fIarguments\fP\fB>\fP\fB]\fP
.fi
.RE
.LP
where tha <\fIseparator\fP> can be zero or mo' <blank>s.
.LP
In tha followin descriptions, tha application shall ensure dat the
argument \fIcommand\fP (but not \fImailx-command)\fP be a
shell command strin fo' realz. Any strang aaight ta tha command interpreter
specified by tha \fISHELL\fP variable when it is invoked as
\fISHELL\fP \fB-c\fP \fIcommand_string\fP shall be valid. Y'all KNOW dat shit, muthafucka! Da command
can be presented as multiple arguments (that is, quoting
is not required).
.LP
Command escapes dat is listed wit \fImsglist\fP or \fImailx-command\fP
arguments is invalid up in Send Mode n' produce
unspecified thangs up in dis biatch.
.TP 7
\fB~!\ \fP \fIcommand\fP
Invoke tha command interpreta specified by \fISHELL\fP wit two arguments:
\fB-c\fP n' \fIcommand\fP; n' then return to
input mode. If tha \fBbang\fP variable is set, each unescaped occurrence
of \fB'!'\fP up in \fIcommand\fP shall be replaced with
the command executed by tha previous \fB!\fP command or \fB~!\fP command
escape.
.TP 7
\fB~.\fP
Simulate end-of-file (terminizzle message input).
.TP 7
\fB~:\ \fP \fImailx-command\fP,\ \fB~_\ \fP \fImailx-command\fP
.sp
Perform tha command-level request.
.TP 7
\fB~?\fP
Write a summary of command escapes.
.TP 7
\fB~A\fP
This shall be equivalent ta \fB~i\ Sign\fP.
.TP 7
\fB~a\fP
This shall be equivalent ta \fB~i\ sign\fP.
.TP 7
\fB~b\ \fP \fIname\fP...
Add tha \fIname\fPs ta tha blind carbon copy ( \fBBcc\fP) list.
.TP 7
\fB~c\ \fP \fIname\fP...
Add tha \fIname\fPs ta tha carbon copy ( \fBCc\fP) list.
.TP 7
\fB~d\fP
Read up in tha dead-letta file. Right back up in yo muthafuckin ass. See \fIDEAD\fP fo' a thugged-out description of
this file.
.TP 7
\fB~e\fP
Invoke tha editor, as specified by tha \fIEDITOR\fP environment variable,
on tha partial message.
.TP 7
\fB~f\ [\fP\fImsglist\fP\fB]\fP
Forward tha specified lyrics. Da specified lyrics shall be inserted
into tha current message without alteration. I aint talkin' bout chicken n' gravy biatch. This
command escape also shall bang message headaz tha fuck into tha message
with field selection affected by tha \fBdiscard\fP,
\fBignore\fP, n' \fBretain\fP commands.
.TP 7
\fB~F\ [\fP\fImsglist\fP\fB]\fP
This shall be tha equivalent of tha \fB~f\fP command escape, except
that all headaz shall be included up in tha message,
regardless of previous \fBdiscard\fP, \fBignore\fP, n' \fBretain\fP
commands.
.TP 7
\fB~h\fP
If standard input be a terminal, prompt fo' a \fBSubject\fP line and
the \fBTo\fP, \fBCc\fP, n' \fBBcc\fP lists, n' you can put dat on yo' toast. Other
implementation-defined headaz may also be presented fo' editing.
If tha field is freestyled wit a initial value, it can be edited
as if it had just been typed.
.TP 7
\fB~i\ \fP \fIstring\fP
Insert tha value of tha named variable, followed by a <newline>, into
the text of tha message. If tha strang is unset or
null, tha message shall not be chizzled.
.TP 7
\fB~m\ [\fP\fImsglist\fP\fB]\fP
Insert tha specified lyrics tha fuck into tha message, prefixin non-empty
lines wit tha strang up in tha \fBindentprefix\fP variable.
This command escape also shall bang message headaz tha fuck into tha message,
with field selection affected by tha \fBdiscard\fP,
\fBignore\fP, n' \fBretain\fP commands.
.TP 7
\fB~M\ [\fP\fImsglist\fP\fB]\fP
This shall be tha equivalent of tha \fB~m\fP command escape, except
that all headaz shall be included up in tha message,
regardless of previous \fBdiscard\fP, \fBignore\fP, n' \fBretain\fP
commands.
.TP 7
\fB~p\fP
Write tha message bein entered. Y'all KNOW dat shit, muthafucka! If tha message is longer than \fBcrt\fP
lines (see Internal
Variablez up in mailx ), tha output shall be paginated as busted lyrics bout for
the \fIPAGER\fP variable.
.TP 7
\fB~q\fP
Quit (see tha \fBquit\fP command) from input mode by simulatin an
interrupt. If tha body of tha message aint empty, the
partial message shall be saved up in tha dead-letta file. Right back up in yo muthafuckin ass. See \fIDEAD\fP
for a thugged-out description of dis file.
.TP 7
\fB~r\ \fP \fIfile\fP,\ \fB~<\ \fP
\fIfile\fP,\ \fB~r\ !\fP\fIcommand\fP,\ \fB~<\ !\fP\fIcommand\fP
.sp
Read up in tha file specified by tha pathname \fIfile\fP. If tha argument
begins wit a exclamation mark ( \fB'!'\fP ), tha rest
of tha strang shall be taken as a arbitrary system command; tha command
interpreta specified by \fISHELL\fP shall be invoked
with two arguments: \fB-c\fP n' \fIcommand\fP. Da standard output
of \fIcommand\fP shall be banged tha fuck into tha message.
.TP 7
\fB~s\ \fP \fIstring\fP
Set tha subject line ta \fIstring\fP.
.TP 7
\fB~t\ \fP \fIname\fP...
Add tha given \fIname\fPs ta tha \fBTo\fP list.
.TP 7
\fB~v\fP
Invoke tha full-screen editor, as specified by tha \fIVISUAL\fP environment
variable, on tha partial message.
.TP 7
\fB~w\ \fP \fIfile\fP
Write tha partial message, without tha header, onto tha file named
by tha pathname \fIfile\fP. Da file shall be pimped or
the message shall be appended ta it if tha file exists.
.TP 7
\fB~x\fP
Exit as wit \fB~q\fP, except tha message shall not be saved up in the
dead-letta file.
.TP 7
\fB~|\ \fP \fIcommand\fP
Pipe tha body of tha message all up in tha given \fIcommand\fP by invoking
the command interpreta specified by \fISHELL\fP
with two arguments: \fB-c\fP n' \fIcommand\fP. If tha \fIcommand\fP
returns a successful exit status, tha standard output of
the command shall replace tha message. Otherwise, tha message shall
remain unchanged. Y'all KNOW dat shit, muthafucka! If tha \fIcommand\fP fails, a error message
givin tha exit status shall be written.
.sp
.SH EXIT STATUS
.LP
When tha \fB-e\fP option is specified, tha followin exit joints are
returned:
.TP 7
\ 0
Mail was found.
.TP 7
>0
Mail was not found or a error occurred.
.sp
.LP
Otherwise, tha followin exit joints is returned:
.TP 7
\ 0
Successful completion; note dat dis status implies dat all lyrics
were \fIsent\fP yo, but it gives no assurances dat any of
them was straight-up \fIdelivered\fP.
.TP 7
>0
An error occurred.
.sp
.SH CONSEQUENCES OF ERRORS
.LP
When up in input mode (Receive Mode) or Send Mode:
.IP " *" 3
If a error is encountered processin a cold-ass lil command escape (see Command
Escapes up in mailx ), a
diagnostic message shall be freestyled ta standard error, n' tha message
bein composed may be modified yo, but dis condizzle shall not
prevent tha message from bein sent.
.LP
.IP " *" 3
Other errors shall prevent tha bustin  of tha message.
.LP
.LP
When up in command mode:
.IP " *" 3
Default.
.LP
